This article is a notice from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, stating the continuation of the national emergency with respect to the situation in or in relation to the Democratic Republic of the Congo. The national emergency was declared on October 27, 2006, due to the widespread violence and atrocities in the country that posed a threat to regional stability. The measures adopted to deal with this emergency, which included blocking the property of certain individuals contributing to the conflict, must continue beyond October 27, 2012. The notice states that the national emergency will be continued for another year, in accordance with the National Emergencies Act.